you would still need to actually set one of the other methods

No, you don't need anything else after setDefinedSize(false) because that is the happy path - same as just setting
grid.setDataSource(query -> myBackend.fetch(query.getOffset(), query.getLimit());
This also has the shorthand of withUndefinedSize() since then people who used data provider can do
grid.setDataSource(myOldDataProvider).withUndefinedSize();

